U.S. stock futures were higher ahead of the open on Tuesday following U.S. and European efforts to stabilize the banking system.
The ripples of the bank failures comes on the heels of the Federal Reserve‚Äôs next interest rate decision Wednesday. Its policy meeting kicks off Tuesday.
Futures tied to the S&P 500 (
) added 0.6%, while futures on the Dow Jones Industrial Average (
) gained 0.7%. Contracts on the technology-heavy Nasdaq Composite (
