Bond yields are rising, ‚Äúpotentially indicating less of a recessionary impulse from the banking system,‚Äù according to the US Market Intelligence team at JPMorgan. The yield on the benchmark 10-year U.S. Treasury note rose 3.5% Tuesday morning. On the front end of the yield curve, two-year yields jumped to 4.1%.
